<F P=106> [Article by Ya.F. Kotenok and O.G. Gavrilov, Pedagogical </F>
Institute imeni V.I. Lenin; UDC 614.718-078] 
  [Abstract] A portable device has been designed for 
bacteriologic air sampling at positive and negative 
temperatures. The device (M-15) consists of an intake inlets, an 
aerosol generation chamber, and a chamber for trapping bacteria 
on neutral granules coated with 1.5-2.0% starch solution 
for 
adhesiveness. Subsequent sample recovery and routine 
bacteriology yield bacterial counts per cubic meter of air. 
Figures 1; tables 3; references 6 (Russian). 

