<H3> <TI>   Impact of Xenogeneic Splenic Homogenates on Infected Wounds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Impact of Xenogeneic Splenic Homogenates on Infected Wounds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   947C0249D Moscow KHIRURGIYA in Russian No. 11, Nov 93 
(manuscript received 13 May 91) pp 16-19 </F>

<F P=103> 947C0249D </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KHIRURGIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


